cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of a new physical random access channel for NB-IoT, which is a cellular technology for low-power IoT devices. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes receiver algorithms for NPRACH detection and time-of-arrival estimation, which involves processing and analyzing signals. This is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses the design and performance of a new random access preamble for NB-IoT, which is a communication technology. This falls under the domain of communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new design for NB-IoT systems, which involves control and management of devices. This is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper presents simulation results on NPRACH performance, which involves processing and analyzing signals. This is related to multimedia.
